The paper deals with permutation patterns and pattern avoidance, which are topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The algorithms presented in the paper involve computational complexity and running time analysis, which are topics in computational complexity (cs.CC) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the special case of Jordan-permutations, which are related to computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.GT).
